                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d29">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00/2564: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Commissioner in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-11T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 11, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. Your 6, August 9, 3 p.m.</p>
                <p>The position taken by you is fully approved. I have just informed Assistant
                    Secretary of the Navy Roosevelt that you were appointed Commissioner by the
                    President with full powers to carry on negotiations with the Dominican leaders,
                    and that no changes are to be made in the plan except such as may be made by
                    you, in your discretion, in consultation with the Dominican leaders. Assistant
                    Secretary Roosevelt stated that he had sent no instructions to Admiral Robison
                    to make any modifications in the plan, and that he will immediately instruct him
                    that no changes are to be proposed save as you may see fit to suggest them in
                    the course of your negotiations, that you have full authority and that he should
                    cooperate with you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
